There seems to be an issue in understanding there.    If you click on the Change Objects link in the proposal, the original object in question is clearly labeled as a Value Set, NOT a code system.   This is at link [http://terminology.hl7.org/ValueSet/v3-Race] 
[https://bitbucket.hl7.org/projects/UTG/repos/utg/commits/6180b4ab38a28d8a30c75de92413555c2da411e6]    A value set is NEVER the source of truth for concepts.    If you examine the CLD, the codes are drawn from code system Include these codes as defined in {{[http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v3-Race|https://terminology.hl7.org/3.0.0/CodeSystem-v3-Race.html].   Thus it sems that this is actually the object to be deprecated.}}

{{I do see that the v3 code system (an artifact pushlished im the v3 coremif for decades) does have its status set to 'retired', but the change to the manifests to remove it from the active v3 code systems list to the retired code systems list was not done.}}

{{My final point is that UTG ticket change proposal Sponsors should be HL7 Workgroups or HL7 Affiliates except under some special circumstances that must be documented.   This may not be clear in the current instructions; I think since this is a US Realm proposal that the US Realm steering committee WG should be the proposal sponsor (it is fine to indicate that the reason behind it is from needs of BCBSA); there should also be a link in the Description to the minuted decision to approve the ticket.}}

{{}}

